  <!-- Intro Section -->
  <section class="homecoming-intro-section-homecomeplanningsir" data-aos="fade-up">
    <p>
      In Sri Lankan tradition, the homecoming marks the bride’s symbolic and heartfelt return—not to her own home, but to begin her new life in the groom’s household. Held a few days after the wedding, this beautiful ceremony is a continuation of the celebration, where the bride is warmly welcomed by her new family. It's a moment filled with tradition, joy, and connection—where rituals are performed, gifts are exchanged, and families blend through laughter, blessings, and shared meals. Whether grand or intimate, the homecoming signifies love’s new chapter and the union of two families into one.
    </p>
  </section>

